### Create Encrypted RxDatabase with Web-Crypto (RxDB)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/encryption.html

Utilize the rxdb-premium plugin to wrap an RxStorage with Web-Crypto API encryption. This provides enhanced security and performance for database encryption.

```javascript
import { wrappedKeyEncryptionWebCryptoStorage, createPassword } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/encryption-web-crypto';
import { getRxStorageIndexedDB } from 'rxdb-premium/plugins/storage-indexeddb';
import { createRxDatabase } from 'rxdb';

// Wrap the normal storage with the encryption plugin
const encryptedIndexedDbStorage = wrappedKeyEncryptionWebCryptoStorage({
    storage: getRxStorageIndexedDB()
});

const myPasswordObject = {
    // Algorithm can be oneOf: 'AES-CTR' | 'AES-CBC' | 'AES-GCM'
    algorithm: 'AES-CTR',
    password: 'myRandomPasswordWithMin8Length'
};

// Create an encrypted database
const db = await createRxDatabase({
    name: 'mydatabase',
    storage: encryptedIndexedDbStorage,
    password: myPasswordObject
});
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Schema for Encrypted Attachments (RxDB)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/encryption.html

Enable encryption for attachments by setting `encrypted: true` within the `attachments` property of your RxDB schema.

```javascript
const mySchema = {
    version: 0,
    type: 'object',
    properties: {
        /* ... */
    },
    attachments: {
        encrypted: true // if true, the attachment-data will be encrypted with the db-password
    }
};
```

--------------------------------

### Create RxCollection with Encrypted Property (RxDB)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/encryption.html

Define a schema to encrypt specific properties within an RxCollection. Add the property name to the 'encrypted' array in the schema definition.

```javascript
const schema = {
  version: 0,
  primaryKey: 'id',
  type: 'object',
  properties: {
    id: {
      type: 'string',
      maxLength: 100
    },
    secret: {
      type: 'string'
    }
  },
  required: ['id'],
  encrypted: ['secret']
};

await db.addCollections({
  myDocuments: {
    schema
  }
});
```

