### Insert and Query Encrypted Data in RxDB

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/articles/react-native-encryption.md

Demonstrates how to initialize an encrypted RxDB database, insert documents with encrypted fields, and query using non-encrypted fields. Encrypted fields can only be accessed after decryption post-query.

```javascript
async () => {
    const db = await initEncryptedDatabase();

    // Insert encrypted data
    const doc = await db.secureData.insert({
        id: 'mySecretId',
        normalField: 'foobar',
        secretField: 'This is top secret data'
    });

    // Query encrypted data by its primary key or non-encrypted fields
    const fetchedDoc = await db.secureData.findOne({
        selector: {
            normalField: 'foobar'
        }
    }).exec(true);
    console.log(fetchedDoc.secretField); // 'This is top secret data'

    // Update data
    await fetchedDoc.patch({
        secretField: 'Updated secret data'
    });
}
```

